column5: Hey all, was thinking of going down to Innisfil and check things out....not sure if I'll do much fishing if any.  Does anyone care to join me for a bit?  I'm not a big fan of the ice and even less so when I'm alone.  Maureen
Bring snowshoes, snowblower or tie a dog to each foot, looks like another foot of snow coming tonight, this is nuts.
The  Gofishont Hardwater Challenge is being held on Saturday February 16/08 from the same park we will be having the Fishing for Tyler M&G on Saturday February 23/08 so you won't be alone...
Thanks Beans, at least I won't have to drill a hole then if I don't want to fish   heck might not have to if I do want to fish   I just have to watch where I step  Maureen
I'd love to join you Moe but I have to work at the CSAAA show all day Saturday & Sunday and will be spending Saturday night in Toronto. If you do get out, good luck.
Best of luck ... the perch are deep ... literally 50-80 feet
